<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880915-0038 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Noted... </HL><SO> </SO><CO> WCI WNEWS ATCMA TL </CO><TEXT>   VENTURE: Movie producer David Puttnam joined a new motion picture joint venture to be financed by Warner Communications Inc., British and Japanese investors. Mr. Puttnam's Enigma Productions will have a revolving $50 million fund for production costs of six or seven movies under a four-year contract.    WHO'S NEWS: Michael E. Luftman was named vice president of corporate public affairs for American Television andamp; Communications Corp., Stamford, Conn. Mr. Luftman was corporate press information manager at the cable television operator, which is 82% owned by Time Inc. </TEXT></DOC>